FBIS4-42350 "drweu106_h_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 GERMANY Minesweeping Operations To Finish by `End of Year' Minesweeping Operations To Finish by `End of Year' AU0106122994 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network in German 1100 GMT 1 Jun 94 AU0106122994 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network German BFN [Text] Mine-sweeping operations along the former inner German border will be completed by the end of the year. This is what a spokesman for the responsible authority in Magdeburg told DDP. He said the blasters were primarily removing plastic mines with loads of up to 200 grams. Between 1961 and 1985, more than 1.5 million mines were reportedly laid along the former border.
